OL,3,C'Absolutely reckless' to give murderer
OL,4,Ccompassionate release, family warns
OL,6,F"Anybody that would make that decision
OL,7,Fto have him released, potentially the
OL,8,Fblood is on their hands.
OL,10,F"He could strike again, with anybody.
OL,11,FIt might not be a revengeful or
OL,12,Fvengeful attack on us or our family.
OL,13,FIt could be the nurse at the hospice
OL,14,Fthat he's released to, it could be the
OL,15,Fwoman at the corner shop."
OL,17,FHe added: "This is about everybody and
OL,18,Fabout why on earth would they take
OL,19,Fsuch a ridiculous risk for someone
OL,20,Fthat has a history of this."
