OL,6,FMr Hoskins added: "He should be denied
OL,7,Fthat privilege. Some people might say
OL,8,Fat least give him the dignity of dying
OL,9,Fon the outside.
OL,11,F"Unfortunately, my mum doesn't have
OL,12,Fthat luxury of the 30 years, 40 years
OL,13,Fthat he stole when he killed her in
OL,14,F1996."
OL,16,FA Ministry of Justice spokesperson
OL,17,Fsaid: "Glenda Hoskins' murder was a
OL,18,Fhorrific crime and our thoughts remain
OL,19,Fwith her family and friends.
